CSS Grid contains: 
  1. Grid Container (Parent Element)
    - contain grid items
    - applies overarching styling & positioning to them
  2. Grid items
  
EX: 
.html
<div class="grid">
  <div class="box a">A</div>
  <div class="box b>B</div>
  <div class="box c>C</div>
</div>

.css
.grid{
display
}

.box {
}

.a {
}

Properties that define the number and sizes of columns and/or rows
  - grid-template-columns: 100px 1fr 10%
  - grid-template-rows: 100px 1fr 10%
  - grid-template: 100px 1fr 10%/ 100px 1fr 10% (rows/columns)
  
Space between rows/columns
- grid-column-gap: 5px
- grid-row-gap: 5px
- grid-gap: 20px 10px (row column)

Make elements span certain rows/columns of the grid
- grid-row-start: 4
- grid-row-end: 6
- grid row: 4/ 6

- grid-column-start: 4
- grid-column-end: 6
- grid column: 4/ 6

- grid-area: 2/3/4/5
(grid-row-start/grid-column-start/grid-row-end/grid-column-end)
